org.jcvi.jillion.fasta.pos

Class AbstractPositionSequenceFastaRecordVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.fasta.pos.AbstractPositionSequenceFastaRecordVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FastaRecordVisitor

    public abstract class AbstractPositionSequenceFastaRecordVisitor
extends Object
implements FastaRecordVisitor
    AbstractPositionSequenceFastaRecordVisitor is an abstract implementation of FastaRecordVisitor that will collect the visit methods for a single fasta record and build an instance of PositionFastaRecord. When FastaRecordVisitor.visitEnd() is called, the PositionFastaRecord is built and the abstract method visitRecord(PositionFastaRecord) will be called.

    A new instance of this class should be used for each fasta record to be visited. This class is not threadsafe.

    Author:
    dkatzel
